{# Ventilation advisor — should you open a window? Pure decision math; entity reads (states/now)
   stay in the caller (bedroom_window_advisor, files/automations.yaml). Returns 'stale' (indoor air
   is stale, ventilate), 'cool' (free cooling available), or 'none' (don't suggest). Every non-'none'
   verdict REQUIRES outdoor air to be under the safe caps (pm_safe / pm10_safe) — so the system can
   never advise ventilating into unsafe air (the smoke guard). Args coerce inside (like lighting.jinja)
   so a caller may pass strings or numbers. Unavailable -> safe 'none'.
   Unit-tested in tests/test_ventilation_macros.py. Tune the comfort band / cool delta / PM cap here.
   'stale' outranks 'cool' when both apply. #}
{%- macro ventilation_advice(indoor_temp, outdoor_temp, indoor_pm, outdoor_pm, air_stale,
                             outdoor_pm10=0, comfort_lo=55, comfort_hi=78, cool_delta=5,
                             pm_safe=25, pm10_safe=50) -%}
{%- set it = indoor_temp | float(0) -%}
{%- set ot = outdoor_temp | float(999) -%}
{%- set ip = indoor_pm | float(0) -%}
{%- set op = outdoor_pm | float(999) -%}
{%- set op10 = outdoor_pm10 | float(999) -%}
{%- set stale = air_stale | bool -%}
{# Smoke guard: block on fine PM2.5 over its cap OR coarse PM10 over its own (higher) cap — the two
   absolute air-quality gates. There is deliberately NO relative "outdoor dirtier than indoors" term:
   a HEPA purifier drives indoor PM near zero, so any such term vetoed CO2/cooling ventilation on
   normal safe-but-moderate outdoor air (e.g. outdoor 18 vs a scrubbed indoor 2) — the recurring
   regression this macro kept re-introducing across three fixes (a relative margin, then a relative
   floor, both leaky). Objectively-safe outdoor air (under the caps) is fine to bring in; the purifier
   re-scrubs it. Genuinely bad air is caught by the absolute pm_safe / pm10_safe caps alone. The
   indoor_pm arg is retained for call-site compatibility but no longer gates. #}
{%- if op > pm_safe or op10 > pm10_safe -%}none
{%- elif stale and comfort_lo <= ot <= comfort_hi -%}stale
{%- elif it > comfort_hi and (it - ot) >= cool_delta -%}cool
{%- else -%}none
{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro -%}
